A terror attack in Jaipur, India, killed 80 and injured 200, prompting global condemnation.
British and French officials expressed solidarity with India in the fight against terrorism.
The bombings, attributed to Islamic militants, have reignited tensions between India and Pakistan.
The US also condemned the attacks, emphasizing support for India's anti-terrorism efforts.
The series of bombings in Jaipur follows a pattern of violence across India in recent years, with authorities urging calm amidst fears of escalating Hindu-Muslim conflict.
The international community stands united in denouncing these senseless acts of violence.
